---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
import Alert from '../../components/Alert.astro';
import Accordion from '../../components/Accordion.astro';
---

<Layout
  title="Troubleshooting: Legitimate Sites Being Blocked"
  description="Fix false positives where important websites are blocked incorrectly. Learn how to whitelist sites and adjust filter sensitivity."
>
  <Breadcrumb />

  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 py-8 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <header class="pb-6 border-b-4 border-blue-600 dark:border-blue-500 mb-8">
      <div
        class="inline-block px-4 py-2 rounded-full text-sm font-semibold mb-4 bg-green-100 dark:bg-green-900 text-green-800 dark:text-green-100"
      >
        Beginner
      </div>
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-extrabold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-3 leading-tight">
        Legitimate Sites Being Blocked
      </h1>
      <p class="text-xl text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400 leading-relaxed mb-4">
        Important websites are being blocked incorrectly (false positives). Learn how to whitelist sites and adjust
        filtering.
      </p>
      <div class="flex gap-6 flex-wrap text-base text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-400">
        <span>‚è±Ô∏è Time Required: 5-15 minutes</span>
        <span>üîß Difficulty: Beginner</span>
      </div>
    </header>

    <Alert type="warning">
      <strong>Before Unblocking:</strong> Verify the site is actually legitimate. Malicious sites often use trustworthy-looking
      names. Check the URL carefully for misspellings.
    </Alert>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Common False Positives</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
        These legitimate sites are frequently blocked by overly aggressive filtering:
      </p>

      <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Healthcare:</strong> Medical information sites, pharmacy portals</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Education:</strong> School websites, online learning platforms</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Finance:</strong> Banks, investment platforms, cryptocurrency exchanges</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Government:</strong> Tax portals, DMV, social services</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Shopping:</strong> Clothing retailers (sometimes blocked due to model photos)</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Cloud storage:</strong> Google Drive, Dropbox, OneDrive sharing links</li>
        <li class="mb-2"><strong>Forums:</strong> Reddit, Quora, Stack Overflow (user-generated content)</li>
      </ul>

      <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
        False positives occur because filtering uses category-based blocking. A site might be classified in a blocked
        category even if it has legitimate uses.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Solutions by Filtering Method</h2>

      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-0 mb-4">
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl"
            >1</span
          >
          OpenDNS Filtering
        </h3>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">
          Option A: Whitelist Individual Sites
        </h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Log into your OpenDNS account at <strong>dashboard.opendns.com</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Select your network configuration</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Navigate to <strong>Web Content Filtering</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Scroll to bottom: <strong>"Manage Individual Domains"</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Under <strong>"Always Allow"</strong>, add the domain</li>
          <li class="mb-2">
            Example: Add <code
              class="bg-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-950 text-green-300 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-mono"
              >reddit.com</code
            > if needed for schoolwork
          </li>
          <li class="mb-2">Click <strong>"Add Domain"</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Wait 3-5 minutes for changes to propagate</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">
          Option B: Adjust Category Sensitivity
        </h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Dashboard ‚Üí <strong>Web Content Filtering</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Review blocked categories</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Uncheck categories that are blocking too broadly</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Example: If educational sites are blocked, uncheck "Forums/Bulletin Boards"</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Save changes</li>
        </ol>

        <Alert type="info">
          <strong>Note:</strong> OpenDNS FamilyShield (free version) cannot be customized. Upgrade to OpenDNS Home (free
          with signup) for whitelist control.
        </Alert>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-0 mb-4">
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl"
            >2</span
          >
          CleanBrowsing Filtering
        </h3>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">
          Free Filters (No Customization):
        </h4>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
          CleanBrowsing's free filters cannot be customized. Options:
        </p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">
            <strong>Switch filter levels:</strong> Use "Adult" filter instead of "Family" filter (less restrictive)
          </li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Upgrade to paid:</strong> $5/month for custom whitelists</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Device-specific bypass:</strong> Change DNS on specific devices only</li>
        </ul>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Paid Plan Whitelisting:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Log into CleanBrowsing dashboard</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Select your filter profile</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Navigate to <strong>"Allowed Domains"</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add domain to allow list</li>
          <li class="mb-2">
            Can use wildcards: <code
              class="bg-gray-900 dark:bg-gray-950 text-green-300 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm font-mono"
              >*.example.com</code
            > allows all subdomains
          </li>
          <li class="mb-2">Save and wait 2-3 minutes</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-0 mb-4">
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl"
            >3</span
          >
          Router Parental Controls
        </h3>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Most Routers:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Log into router admin panel</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Navigate to <strong>Parental Controls</strong> or <strong>Security</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">
            Find <strong>"Allowed Sites"</strong>, <strong>"Whitelist"</strong>, or <strong>"Exceptions"</strong>
          </li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add the domain</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Apply changes and reboot router if necessary</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">ASUS Routers:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">AiProtection ‚Üí Parental Controls</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Select profile</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Content Filter ‚Üí <strong>"URL Filter Exception"</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add allowed domain</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Netgear Routers:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Security ‚Üí Parental Controls</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Click managed device</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>"Always Allow"</strong> section</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add website</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">TP-Link Routers:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">HomeCare ‚Üí Parental Controls</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Select profile</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Insights ‚Üí <strong>"Whitelisted"</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add site</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-0 mb-4">
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl"
            >4</span
          >
          Software Filtering (Qustodio, Net Nanny, etc.)
        </h3>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Qustodio:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Log into family portal at <strong>family.qustodio.com</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Select child's profile</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Rules</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Web Filtering</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Scroll to <strong>"Exceptions"</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>"Always allow these sites"</strong> ‚Üí Add domain</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Changes apply immediately</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Net Nanny:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Log into online dashboard</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Select family member</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Web Settings</strong> ‚Üí <strong>"Allow List"</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add website</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Can allow temporarily or permanently</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Bark:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Bark app or dashboard</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Child's profile ‚Üí <strong>Screen Time</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Website Rules</strong> ‚Üí <strong>"Allowed Websites"</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add site</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Circle:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Circle app</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Select profile</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Filter Level</strong> ‚Üí <strong>"Custom"</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>"Allowed Sites"</strong> ‚Üí Add domain</li>
        </ol>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 border-2 border-gray-200 dark:border-gray-700 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
        <h3 class="flex items-center gap-3 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-0 mb-4">
          <span
            class="inline-flex items-center justify-center w-10 h-10 bg-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-full font-bold text-xl"
            >5</span
          >
          Device-Level Controls
        </h3>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">iOS Screen Time:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Settings ‚Üí Screen Time ‚Üí Select child/device</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Content & Privacy Restrictions</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Content Restrictions</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">
            <strong>Web Content</strong> ‚Üí <strong>"Allowed Websites Only"</strong> or <strong
              >"Limit Adult Websites"</strong
            >
          </li>
          <li class="mb-2">Under <strong>"Always Allow"</strong> section, tap <strong>Add Website</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Enter site name and URL</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Done</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Android Family Link:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Family Link app on parent device</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Select child</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Manage Settings</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Filters on Google Chrome</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Manage Sites</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Approved</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add website</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">Windows Family Safety:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Visit <strong>account.microsoft.com/family</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Select family member</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Content Restrictions</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Web Browsing</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Under <strong>"Always allow these"</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add URL</li>
        </ol>

        <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold text-gray-800 dark:text-gray-200 mt-4 mb-3">macOS Screen Time:</h4>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">System Settings ‚Üí Screen Time</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Select user</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Content & Privacy</strong> ‚Üí <strong>Web Content</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Allowed Websites Only</strong> ‚Üí Add <strong>+</strong></li>
          <li class="mb-2">Enter site details</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Temporary Access Solutions</h2>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
        When permanent whitelisting isn't appropriate but temporary access is needed:
      </p>

      <div class="flex flex-col gap-4 mt-6">
        <Accordion title="Timed Whitelist (Preferred)">
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
            Some systems support temporary exceptions:
          </p>
          <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Net Nanny:</strong> "Allow for 1 hour" button when site is blocked</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Bark:</strong> Can approve individual site access requests</li>
            <li class="mb-2"><strong>Qustodio:</strong> "Pause Protection" for 5-60 minutes</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
            After time expires, filtering automatically resumes.
          </p>
        </Accordion>

        <Accordion title="Supervised Browsing">
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Unblock temporarily while supervising:</p>
          <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <li class="mb-2">Disable filtering temporarily</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Sit with child while they access needed content</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Re-enable filtering when done</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
            Appropriate for school projects requiring research on sensitive topics.
          </p>
        </Accordion>

        <Accordion title="Alternative Device">
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
            Use an unfiltered device for specific tasks:
          </p>
          <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <li class="mb-2">Parent's phone or laptop (supervised)</li>
            <li class="mb-2">School chromebook (school's filtering only)</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Public library computer</li>
          </ul>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
            Maintains filtering on child's personal devices.
          </p>
        </Accordion>

        <Accordion title="Request System">
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">Teach kids to request access:</p>
          <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
            <li class="mb-2">Child encounters blocked site</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Takes screenshot or notes URL</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Asks parent to review</li>
            <li class="mb-2">Parent decides whether to whitelist</li>
          </ol>
          <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
            Builds communication and trust while maintaining protection.
          </p>
        </Accordion>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Decision Framework: To Unblock or Not?</h2>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-6 mb-4">‚úÖ Unblock If:</h3>
      <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li class="mb-2">Required for school/work</li>
        <li class="mb-2">Clearly legitimate business/service</li>
        <li class="mb-2">False positive due to broad category blocking</li>
        <li class="mb-2">Age-appropriate content for your child</li>
        <li class="mb-2">Reputable source (government, major brand, educational institution)</li>
      </ul>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-6 mb-4">‚ö†Ô∏è Proceed Cautiously If:</h3>
      <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li class="mb-2">User-generated content site (can contain anything)</li>
        <li class="mb-2">Social media platform</li>
        <li class="mb-2">Anonymous forum or imageboard</li>
        <li class="mb-2">Dating or relationship advice site</li>
        <li class="mb-2">Site discussing mature topics (even educationally)</li>
      </ul>
      <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
        <em>Consider: Supervised access only, not permanent whitelist</em>
      </p>

      <h3 class="text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mt-6 mb-4">‚ùå Don't Unblock If:</h3>
      <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
        <li class="mb-2">You're unsure what the site contains</li>
        <li class="mb-2">URL looks suspicious or misspelled</li>
        <li class="mb-2">Child can't articulate a legitimate reason</li>
        <li class="mb-2">Site bypasses or discusses bypassing filters</li>
        <li class="mb-2">Proxy site, VPN service, or "unblock" tool</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="mt-10">
      <h2 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 dark:text-white mb-6">Common Scenarios</h2>

      <Accordion title="Reddit blocked but needed for homework">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Teacher assigned research on specific subreddit, but Reddit is blocked.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3"><strong>Solutions:</strong></p>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Best:</strong> Supervised access on parent's device</li>
          <li class="mb-2">
            <strong>Alternative:</strong> Whitelist specific subreddit only (if filtering supports subdomain/path filtering)
          </li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Option 3:</strong> Contact teacher about alternative assignment</li>
        </ol>
        <Alert type="warning">
          Don't whitelist all of Reddit - it contains unmoderated content. Specific subreddits only.
        </Alert>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion title="Bank website blocked">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Online banking site flagged as financial/commerce.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
          <strong>Solution:</strong> Always whitelist legitimate financial institutions:
        </p>
        <ol class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">Verify URL is correct (beware of phishing)</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add to permanent whitelist</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Add both www and non-www versions</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Consider whitelisting entire financial category if using DNS filtering</li>
        </ol>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion title="Online shopping sites blocked">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Clothing/shoe retailers blocked due to model photos.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3"><strong>Assessment needed:</strong></p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Major retailers (Target, Old Navy, etc.):</strong> Usually safe to whitelist</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Fashion sites with revealing images:</strong> Supervise first</li>
          <li class="mb-2"><strong>Victoria's Secret, lingerie sites:</strong> Age-dependent decision</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
          Consider: Is online shopping necessary, or can child shop in-store?
        </p>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion title="Educational sites about health/anatomy">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
          <strong>Problem:</strong> Age-appropriate health education sites blocked.
        </p>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
          <strong>Legitimate sites to consider whitelisting:</strong>
        </p>
        <ul class="ml-6 mb-4 text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300">
          <li class="mb-2">KidsHealth.org</li>
          <li class="mb-2">TeensHealth.org</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Planned Parenthood educational resources (age-dependent)</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Mayo Clinic, WebMD</li>
          <li class="mb-2">Approved school health curriculum sites</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
          Better to provide accurate health information than force kids to unsafe sources.
        </p>
      </Accordion>

      <Accordion title="YouTube blocked but need specific educational video">
        <p class="leading-relaxed text-gray-700 dark:text-gray-300 mb-3">
          <strong>Problem:</strong> YouTube entirely blocked, but teacher assigned a specific video.
